{"type":"stream_event","event":{"type":"content_block_delta","index":3,"delta":{"type":"input_json_delta","partial_json":"{\"description\":\"Technical review week_06\",\"prompt\":\"You are the technical-reviewer agent for the Java software engineering textbook. \\n\\nYour task: Perform a **fresh** technical review of week_06 (单元测试与测试策略 / Unit Testing and Test Strategy).\\n\\n**Context files to read:**\\n- chapters/week_06/CHAPTER.md\\n- chapters/week_06/ASSIGNMENT.md\\n- chapters/week_06/RUBRIC.md\\n- chapters/week_06/ANCHORS.yml\\n- chapters/week_06/TERMS.yml\\n- chapters/week_06/examples/ (all example files)\\n- chapters/week_06/starter_code/src/main/java/ (source code)\\n- chapters/week_06/starter_code/src/test/java/ (test code)\\n- shared/style_guide.md\\n- shared/glossary.yml\\n\\n**Review dimensions:**\\n1. **Concept correctness** (概念正确性): Are the JUnit 5, testing lifecycle, parameterized testing, coverage concepts accurately explained?\\n2. **Code correctness** (代码正确性): Do the code examples compile and run? Are they using current Java 17 + JUnit 5.11.x best practices?\\n3. **Answer correctness** (答案正确性): Are the assignment solutions and rubric criteria correct?\\n4. **Pedagogical alignment** (教学法对齐): Does the chapter follow CLAUDE.md constraints (narrative quality, cognitive load, character consistency)?\\n5. **Exercise quality** (练习题质量): Are the assignments well-designed with appropriate difficulty levels?\\n\\n**Output format:**\\nReturn a structured report with S1-S4 severity levels:\\n- **S1 (Critical)**: Must fix before release (blocking)\\n- **S2 (Major)**: Should fix before release (blocking)\\n- **S3 (Moderate)**: Should fix (blocking per current instructions)\\n- **S4 (Minor)**: Nice to have (blocking per current instructions)\\n\\nFor each issue, provide:\\n- Location (file:line or section)\\n- Description\\n- Suggested fix\\n\\n**Important**: This is a READ-ONLY review. Do NOT modify any files. Just return your findings as a message.\",\"subagent_type\":\"technical-reviewer\"}"}},"session_id":"5071dd61-4cb8-490e-a97a-6edea443d84b","parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5febeb8b-fc37-42e2-a5b1-349f7020ec61"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_202602250853286b45e52bb7514729","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"glm-5","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_14f9c3afc6df478fbe525d70","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Technical review week_06","prompt":"You are the technical-reviewer agent for the Java software engineering textbook. \n\nYour task: Perform a **fresh** technical review of week_06 (单元测试与测试策略 / Unit Testing and Test Strategy).\n\n**Context files to read:**\n- chapters/week_06/CHAPTER.md\n- chapters/week_06/ASSIGNMENT.md\n- chapters/week_06/RUBRIC.md\n- chapters/week_06/ANCHORS.yml\n- chapters/week_06/TERMS.yml\n- chapters/week_06/examples/ (all example files)\n- chapters/week_06/starter_code/src/main/java/ (source code)\n- chapters/week_06/starter_code/src/test/java/ (test code)\n- shared/style_guide.md\n- shared/glossary.yml\n\n**Review dimensions:**\n1. **Concept correctness** (概念正确性): Are the JUnit 5, testing lifecycle, parameterized testing, coverage concepts accurately explained?\n2. **Code correctness** (代码正确性): Do the code examples compile and run? Are they using current Java 17 + JUnit 5.11.x best practices?\n3. **Answer correctness** (答案正确性): Are the assignment solutions and rubric criteria correct?\n4. **Pedagogical alignment** (教学法对齐): Does the chapter follow CLAUDE.md constraints (narrative quality, cognitive load, character consistency)?\n5. **Exercise quality** (练习题质量): Are the assignments well-designed with appropriate difficulty levels?\n\n**Output format:**\nReturn a structured report with S1-S4 severity levels:\n- **S1 (Critical)**: Must fix before release (blocking)\n- **S2 (Major)**: Should fix before release (blocking)\n- **S3 (Moderate)**: Should fix (blocking per current instructions)\n- **S4 (Minor)**: Nice to have (blocking per current instructions)\n\nFor each issue, provide:\n- Location (file:line or section)\n- Description\n- Suggested fix\n\n**Important**: This is a READ-ONLY review. Do NOT modify any files. Just return your findings as a message.","subagent_type":"technical-reviewer"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5071dd61-4cb8-490e-a97a-6edea443d84b","uuid":"470e5313-9f13-4c49-9962-a1cf03ccea8b"}
