{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are the technical-reviewer agent for the Java software engineering textbook. \n\nYour task: Perform a **fresh** technical review of week_06 (单元测试与测试策略 / Unit Testing and Test Strategy).\n\n**Context files to read:**\n- chapters/week_06/CHAPTER.md\n- chapters/week_06/ASSIGNMENT.md\n- chapters/week_06/RUBRIC.md\n- chapters/week_06/ANCHORS.yml\n- chapters/week_06/TERMS.yml\n- chapters/week_06/examples/ (all example files)\n- chapters/week_06/starter_code/src/main/java/ (source code)\n- chapters/week_06/starter_code/src/test/java/ (test code)\n- shared/style_guide.md\n- shared/glossary.yml\n\n**Review dimensions:**\n1. **Concept correctness** (概念正确性): Are the JUnit 5, testing lifecycle, parameterized testing, coverage concepts accurately explained?\n2. **Code correctness** (代码正确性): Do the code examples compile and run? Are they using current Java 17 + JUnit 5.11.x best practices?\n3. **Answer correctness** (答案正确性): Are the assignment solutions and rubric criteria correct?\n4. **Pedagogical alignment** (教学法对齐): Does the chapter follow CLAUDE.md constraints (narrative quality, cognitive load, character consistency)?\n5. **Exercise quality** (练习题质量): Are the assignments well-designed with appropriate difficulty levels?\n\n**Output format:**\nReturn a structured report with S1-S4 severity levels:\n- **S1 (Critical)**: Must fix before release (blocking)\n- **S2 (Major)**: Should fix before release (blocking)\n- **S3 (Moderate)**: Should fix (blocking per current instructions)\n- **S4 (Minor)**: Nice to have (blocking per current instructions)\n\nFor each issue, provide:\n- Location (file:line or section)\n- Description\n- Suggested fix\n\n**Important**: This is a READ-ONLY review. Do NOT modify any files. Just return your findings as a message."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_14f9c3afc6df478fbe525d70","session_id":"5071dd61-4cb8-490e-a97a-6edea443d84b","uuid":"a01230d5-255d-44e9-870a-5d5be5da45d5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are the student-qa agent for the Java software engineering textbook.\n\nYour task: Perform a **fresh** student-perspective review of week_06 (单元测试与测试策略 / Unit Testing and Test Strategy).\n\n**Context files to read:**\n- chapters/week_06/CHAPTER.md\n- shared/characters.yml (for character consistency check)\n- shared/style_guide.md (for narrative quality check)\n\n**Review from a student perspective (undergraduate level, knows basic Java):**\n\n**Four-dimensional scoring:**\n\n1. **叙事流畅度 (Narrative Flow)** [1-5]:\n   - Is the structure varied (not repetitive section patterns)?\n   - Are transitions between sections natural?\n   - Is there \"template feeling\" (模板感)?\n   - Score: 1 (very poor) to 5 (excellent)\n\n2. **趣味性 (Engagement)** [1-5]:\n   - Does the reader want to keep reading?\n   - Are there \"aha moments\" (哦！时刻)?\n   - Are the character appearances (小北/阿码/老潘) engaging?\n   - Score: 1 (boring) to 5 (highly engaging)\n\n3. **知识覆盖 (Knowledge Coverage)** [1-5]:\n   - Are concepts accurate and complete?\n   - Is the code runnable?\n   - Are there 6 new concepts (JUnit basics, lifecycle, exception testing, parameterized tests, coverage, TDD preview)?\n   - Score: 1 (major gaps) to 5 (comprehensive)\n\n4. **认知负荷 (Cognitive Load)** [1-5]:\n   - Is the difficulty manageable?\n   - Are review bridges effective (referencing week_03 防御式编程, week_05 集合框架)?\n   - Is the progression logical?\n   - Score: 1 (overwhelming) to 5 (well-paced)\n\n**Additional checks:**\n- Chapter opening: Is there a quote + \"时代脉搏\" paragraph (200-300 words)?\n- AI sidebars: Are there 2 AI sidebars (one in early section, one in middle)?\n- CampusFlow progress: Is there a \"## CampusFlow 进度\" section?\n- Character appearances: Do 小北/阿码/老潘 each appear at least 2 times?\n- Summary: Is the summary narrative (not bullet list)?\n\n**Output format:**\nReturn:\n1. Four scores (1-5 each) with explanations\n2. Total score (sum /20)\n3. Blocking items (any dimension ≤ 2)\n4. Suggestions for improvement\n\n**Important**: This is a READ-ONLY review. Do NOT modify any files. Just return your findings as a message."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_3310967bf26140b4b25a3c52","session_id":"5071dd61-4cb8-490e-a97a-6edea443d84b","uuid":"6c945beb-cd5d-4e12-a00e-fe3c3e1b1246"}
